parameters: As you sort through the papers on the desk, two
interesting slips catch your attention in the pile.
Two very official looking death certificates with both
your’s and Andrew's names on them plain as day.
"Are these real? Do they look real?"
"It would appear so. Looks the same
"What does this mean? Why would they have these?"
"Why does he do anything at this
point? It's just to hurt us."
"He’s clearly putting in the effort for it."
"Also explains a bit why he and the harlot would screen my calls."
"I don’t think that's the only reason...."
"I-.... Whatever mom just--... let me think."
You hear the sound of a car pulling into the driveway.
"We still don't even have my wedding bands!"
Well, you both seem to be well and truly fucked.
"Guess the reunion is going to happen sooner than we’d hoped."
"Mom, just trust me on this. Let me help you
out the window and I'll be right behind you."
"It's a much bigger problem than you’d
think if we don't get out of here."
"We can get your wedding bands later. I promise."
A window looking out to the backyard.
You push open the window with ease
"Here, you go first. I'll be right behind you."
You help your mother through the window.
You hear the front door open and voices.
"Oh, you know, just came for a surprise visit!"
"B-but how did you even get in??"
"You guys left the door unlocked. You
should really be more careful about that."
"Babe?? Babe, who are you talking to??"
"Your Dad didn’t say you were coming..."
"Y-yeah well... It was kinda a last minute thing, you know."
I was surprised you weren’t home."
"It’s kind of a long story but, Mom and I split up
and I didn’t really have anywhere else to go...."
"B-but where is your mother right now?"
"Never mind that now! Why don’t I fix us all some coffee?"
"You can tell us all about it over a nice warm cup."
"Are you sure that’s a good ide--"
"Great! Let’s head to the living room and I’ll fix us some."
